# Backend Architecture Rules

## AzureDevOpsClient — Single Source of Truth
- ALL HTTP calls to Azure DevOps go through `AzureDevOpsClient`
- Never use raw `fetch` or `axios` directly in service files
- The client handles: auth headers, retries on 429, request logging in dev

## Authentication
- PAT token auth: `Basic ${Buffer.from(':' + pat).toString('base64')}`
- Set on every request via Axios default headers — never per-request

## API Base URLs — Three Domains
- Main: `https://dev.azure.com/{org}`
- Graph/Identity: `https://vssps.dev.azure.com/{org}`
- Entitlements: `https://vsaex.dev.azure.com/{org}`
- Always use API version `7.1` (or `7.1-preview.1` for Graph, `7.1-preview.2` for Entitlements)

## Pagination — Mandatory
- ALL Graph API calls MUST handle `x-ms-continuationtoken` response header
- Loop until the header is absent — never assume one page is complete
- Implement in `AzureDevOpsClient.paginate<T>()` method

## Rate Limiting
- Add 100ms minimum delay between sequential API calls in service methods
- Axios interceptor: on 429 response, wait (retry-after header or exponential backoff), retry max 3x
- Backoff delays: 1000ms, 2000ms, 4000ms

## Caching
- Every public service method that calls the AzDO API checks cache first
- Cache key format: `{org}:{project}:{methodName}:{additionalParams}`
- TTL values come from env config, not hardcoded

## Route Structure
- All routes mounted under `/api`
- Route files only contain: validation, call to service, response formatting
- Business logic lives in service files, never in route handlers

## Error Middleware
- Single global error handler at end of Express middleware chain
- Maps AzDO 401/403 → 401, 429 → 429 with Retry-After, Zod errors → 400, else → 500
- Dev: include stack trace; prod: sanitize

## Project Scoping
- No `AZURE_DEVOPS_DEFAULT_PROJECT` env var exists
- The `/api/projects` endpoint returns the full project list for the org
- All other endpoints require `?project={projectName}` query param (validated, not defaulted)